io.dropwizard.metrics.kafka

Class KafkaReporter

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.codahale.metrics.ScheduledReporter
      • io.dropwizard.metrics.kafka.KafkaReporter
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    com.codahale.metrics.Reporter, Closeable, AutoCloseable

    public final class KafkaReporter
extends com.codahale.metrics.ScheduledReporter
    A reporter which publishes metric values to an Apache Kafka Topic.

    Build Options

    • topic – the topic to which the metrics will be published, defaults to "metrics"
    • serializer – the serializer to use for converting metrics into messages to publish to Kafka. Defaults to the JSONStringSerializer which will convert each metric into a string encoded JSON message keyed by the metric name.
    • filter – a filter to use to restrict which metrics are published to Kafka. Defaults to no filter.
    • rateUnit – dictates the unit in which metrics that report rates are reported in. Defaults to seconds.
    • durationUnit – dictates the unit in which metrics that report durations are reported in. Defaults to milliseconds.

    Note: pay close attention to the serializer the reporter is using! The messages (ProducerRecord instances) it returns must by serializable by your Kafka Producer. The default serializer produces messages with String keys and values; if you are not using the StringSerializer you will need to specify a different serializer (e.g. the JSONByteArraySerializer if you are using ByteArraySerializer.)

    Output

    The exact format of the messages sent to Kafka is dependant upon the serializer in use. By default each metric is sent as its own message (that is: one message per metric) with the key set to the metric name and the value a JSON encoding of the metric properties (with an added timestamp.)

    See the JSONStringSerializer documentation for details of the default message format used by this reporter.
